Pre-heat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Mix all the of the ingredients except the dried fruit together. You can do this in a food processor or by hand in a mixing bowl.When the ingredients are all thoroughly combined, fold in the dried fruit.Spoon the batter mixture into a 1kg/2lb non-stick loaf tin, spread it out evenly and bake it for one and a half hours.When the banana bread has risen, golden-brown on top and cooked through, remove it from the oven and set aside to cool on a wire rack. Slice before serving.